    <question>
        <prompt>The Lost Generation writers were characterized by their:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Patriotic themes</option>
            <option letter="b">Disillusionment with traditional values</option>
            <option letter="c">Support for war</option>
            <option letter="d">Religious devotion</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Lost Generation writers, including Ernest Hemingway and F. Scott Fitzgerald, were characterized by their disillusionment with traditional American values following World War I. Their works expressed themes of alienation, moral uncertainty, and rejection of conventional social values. This literary movement reflected the broader cultural changes and questioning of traditional beliefs in post-war American society.</explanation>
    </question>
